Pulitzer Prize-winning author and University of Florida professor Jack E. Davis will discuss and sign his most recent book, “The Bald Eagle: The Improbable Journey of America’s Bird,” at 6 p.m. Feb. 28 at Lynn Pippenger Hall at the University of South Florida St. Petersburg, 350 Seventh Ave. S. Free. Sorboni Banerjee and Dominique Richardson, co-authors of the new YA thriller “Red as Blood,” will discuss and sign their book at 6:30 p.m. Feb. 28 at Oxford Exchange, 420 W Kennedy Blvd., Tampa. Tickets $5 for admission or $14.95 for admission and a copy of the book at oxfordexchange.com/pages/calendar. Novelists Annabel Monaghan (”Nora Goes Off Script”) and Tracey Enerson Wood (”The War Nurse”) will celebrate the paperback release of their latest books with a discussion and signing at 6:30 p.m. March 2 at Oxford Exchange, 420 W Kennedy Blvd., Tampa. Tickets $5 for admission or $17 for admission and a book at oxfordexchange.com/pages/calendar. Book Talk is a listing of in-person author appearances in the Tampa Bay area in the coming week. To place an item in Book Talk, send author’s name, book title, appearance time, date, venue name and address, admission cost (if any) and a contact phone number to cbancroft@tampabay.com, with “Book Talk” in the subject line. Deadline is 14 days before publication.